  "exec_summary": "The European Banking Authority has published an official translation of amended guidelines on the application of the definition of default under the Capital Requirements Regulation, providing clarity for EU banks. In Belgium, there are no significant regulatory developments this week, but EU-wide, the Anti-Money Laundering Authority notes that know-your-customer failures are a top weakness for EU banks in preventing money laundering. The EBA has also consulted on draft Implementing Technical Standards amending the Implementing Regulation on benchmarking of internal models for the 2027 benchmarking exercise, and issued a final report on Regulatory Technical Standards and Implementing Technical Standards on material acquisitions, transfers, mergers and divisions under the CRD IV Directive.",
